data.chText: （无记名）投票选举；投票表决
data.enText: the system of voting in writing and usually in secret; an occasion on which a vote is held

data.chText: 主席是通过无记名投票选举产生的。
data.enText: The chairperson is chosen by secret ballot .

data.chText: 工会未经会员投票表决不得发动罢工。
data.enText: The union cannot call a strike unless it holds a ballot of members.
ballot paper

data.chText: 选票
data.enText: the piece of paper on which sb marks who they are voting for

data.chText: 有资格的选民中投票的百分比是多少？
data.enText: What percentage of eligible voters cast their ballots ?

data.chText: （选举中的）投票总数
data.enText: the total number of votes in an election

data.chText: 她赢得了投票总数的58.8%。
data.enText: She won 58.8% of the ballot.

data.chText: 要求某人（对某事）无记名投票
data.enText: to ask sb to vote in writing and secretly about sth

data.chText: 工会要求会员对所提议的变革进行无记名投票。
data.enText: The union balloted its members on the proposed changes.

data.chText: 进行无记名投票
data.enText: to vote secretly about sth

data.chText: 工人对是否罢工进行无记名投票表决。
data.enText: The workers balloted for a strike.

data.text: election ♦ vote ♦ poll ♦ referendum ♦ straw poll ♦ ballot ♦ show of hands

data.chText: 以上各词均表示选举或投票表决。
data.enText: These are all words for an event in which people choose a representative or decide sth by voting.
election

data.chText: 指选举、推选，尤指政治选举：
data.enText: an occasion on which people officially choose a political representative or government by voting

data.chText: 上次选举中你把票投给了谁？
data.enText: Who did you vote for in the last election?
vote

data.chText: 指投票、选举、表决：
data.enText: an occasion on which a group of people vote for sb/sth

data.chText: 他们以投票方式决定谁先走。
data.enText: They took a vote on who should go first.
poll

data.chText: （新闻）指选举投票、计票：
data.enText: ( journalism ) the process of voting in an election

data.chText: 他们在投票选举中惨遭失败。
data.enText: They suffered a defeat at the polls .
referendum

data.chText: 指全民投票、全民公决
data.enText: an occasion on which all the adults in a country can vote on a particular issue
straw poll

data.chText: 指非正式民意测验：
data.enText: an occasion on which a number of people are asked in an informal way to give their opinion about sth

data.chText: 我在同事中很快做了一个民意测验看有多少人赞同。
data.enText: I took a quick straw poll among my colleagues to see how many agreed.
ballot

data.chText: 尤指无记名投票选举、投票表决：
data.enText: the system of voting by marking an election paper, especially in secret; an occasion on which a vote is held

data.chText: 领导者将通过无记名投票选举产生。
data.enText: The leader will be chosen by secret ballot.

data.chText: ballot通常用于机构内部的选举，而非公众的投票选举。
data.enText: Ballot is usually used about a vote within an organization rather than an occasion on which the public vote.
show of hands

data.chText: 指举手表决
data.enText: an occasion on which a group of people vote on sth by raising their hands
a national/local/federal/democratic/free/fair election/vote/poll/referendum/ballot
a presidential/parliamentary/congressional/council election/poll
to conduct a(n) election/vote/poll/referendum/straw poll/ballot
to have a(n) election/vote/poll/referendum/straw poll/ballot/show of hands
to hold a(n) election/vote/poll/referendum/straw poll/ballot
take a vote/straw poll/show of hands
a(n) election/referendum campaign/result/victory/defeat

simple_means.memory_skill: ball 球 + ot …人 →〔投票用的〕小球 → 投票

means: 要求某人(对某事)无记名投票

tr: a choice that is made by counting the number of people in favor of each alternative
example: there were only 17 votes in favor of the motion
they allowed just one vote per person

tr: a document listing the alternatives that is used in voting

example: The voters were balloting in this state

value.def: A ballot is a secret vote in which people select a candidate in an election, or express their opinion about something.

example.ex: The result of the ballot will not be known for two weeks...
example.tran: 无记名投票的结果将于两周后公布。

example.ex: Fifty of its members will be elected by direct ballot.

value.tran: 无记名投票；无记名选举；无记名表决

value.def: A ballot is a piece of paper on which you indicate your choice or opinion in a secret vote.

example.ex: Election boards will count the ballots by hand...
example.tran: 选举委员会将人工计票。

example.ex: They succeeded in putting Perot's name on the ballot in Florida.
example.tran: 他们成功地让佩罗在佛罗里达州成为了候选人之一。

value.def: If you ballot a group of people, you find out what they think about a subject by organizing a secret vote.

example.ex: The union said they will ballot members on whether to strike.
example.tran: 工会称他们将要求会员投票表决是否罢工。

value.tran: 在…中间进行无记名投票（或表决）

example.ex: International observers say the balloting was fair.
example.tran: 国际观察员说此次投票是公正的。
